The paper focuses on deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) for vision applications such as object recognition and caption generation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the network's inner workings and transparency, which suggests a possible fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed method involves analyzing feature dependencies across the layer hierarchy, which could also relate to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
